      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your description of feeling hollow and disconnected sounds like dissociation or alexithymia, where emotions feel absent rather than distant or evolving into something new. This sensation of \"being empty\" is often a genuine, painful response to past trauma or prolonged stress that has eroded your sense of self in a way that isn't just growth, but a defense mechanism. Because you mention feeling like you are occupying space that doesn't belong to you, relying on community support or a professional who listens without judgment can help make the absence of feeling a little less isolating.",
